title: the United Kingdom from the European Union (Consequential Provisions) Act
heading: 2. The 29th day of December 2020 is appointed as the day on which
text_raw:
2. The 29th day of December 2020 is appointed as the day on which 
sections 103 and 107 of the Withdrawal of the United Kingdom from the 
European Union (Consequential Provisions) Act 2020 (No. 23 of 2020) shall 
come into operation.

title: the United Kingdom from the European Union (Consequential Provisions) Act
heading: 3. The 31st day of December 2020 at 11.00 p.m. is appointed as the day on
text_raw:
3. The 31st day of December 2020 at 11.00 p.m. is appointed as the day on 
which and the time at which Part 15 (except insofar as it already is in 
operation) of the Withdrawal of the United Kingdom from the European Union 
(Consequential Provisions) Act 2020 shall come into operation. 

GIVEN under my Official Seal, 

23 December, 2020. 

LEO VARADKAR, 

Minister for Enterprise, Trade and Employment. 

Notice of the making of this Statutory Instrument was published in 
“Iris Oifigiúil” of 5th January, 2021.

text_raw:
EXPLANATORY NOTE 

(This note is not part of the Instrument and does not purport to be a legal 
Interpretation) 

This Order provides for the commencement, from 29th December 2020 of 
sections 103 and 107 of the Withdrawal of the United Kingdom from the 
European Union (Consequential Provisions) Act 2020 (No. 23 of 2020), and 
the commencement from 31st December 2020 at 11pm of Part 15 of the 
Withdrawal of the United Kingdom from the European Union (Consequential 
Provisions) Act 2020 (No. 23 of 2020), except insofar as it is already in 
operation.
